™’Щ@a2c9d085a12ab82589dfbd31629478d7adc5449b4dccdc3c2e8db468ff8102b2ЪжTitle: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Nushell 0.36
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.36 of Nu. This release fixes some long-standing issues with history, improves the help system, improves dataframes, and much more.
’Щ@c55a305a7d04c7da2b0107dc72798158478564e16550760f7caf4467e1e5cc51ЪTitle: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.36 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.36.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
’Щ@e68d4d7bb166eba774403d36176da37b7898d9b2ed57011d722a2c45fb2996ebЪ$Title: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Help now has search (fdncred)
Content:
You can now use 
``help -f <term>``
 and search the help for text. This can come in handy if you know roughly what you want but can't remember the name of the command:
```Fenced(Borrowed(""))
> help -f string
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”¬в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
 #  в”‚           name           в”‚                     usage                      в”‚ extra_usage
в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”јв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”јв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”јв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
  0 в”‚ ansi strip               в”‚ strip ansi escape sequences from string        в”‚
  1 в”‚ build-string             в”‚ Builds a string from the arguments.            в”‚
  2 в”‚ dataframe concatenate    в”‚ [Series] Concatenates strings with other array в”‚
  3 в”‚ dataframe contains       в”‚ [Series] Checks if a pattern is contained in a в”‚
    в”‚                          в”‚ string                                         в”‚
  4 в”‚ dataframe replace        в”‚ [Series] Replace the leftmost (sub)string by a в”‚
    в”‚                          в”‚ regex pattern                                  в”‚
...

```
’Щ@d8faa32e8401f44a1b6010f1823f0f1da47f11e7b86e708d69008f571b083868Ъ’Title: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Built-in tutor (sophiajt)
Content:
In addition to the new help search, we've also started to build out a built-in Nushell tutorial. You can navigate by topic or search the help text for a string.
Screenshot showing the tutor command running 'tutor table'
We've only added a few topics so far, but we hope to grow these topics (with your help) over the coming releases.
’Щ@feb2ea10d10368cc50f60d48e078716529aa8fc9ebe33d8efddcd052ba10cc51ЪЬTitle: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: New commands and features
Content:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3917] ``drop nth``
 - drops the given rows (andrasio)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3918] ``PROMPT_STRING``
 environment variable
 - configures the script to run to create the prompt directly from the environment (elferherrera)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3919] ``zip``
 - combine two lists into one list of pairs (andrasio)
’Щ@659f20e59a08ef3c462b19867bc0c570bf2e63e859e24b9edcb8a02715344c17Ъ2Title: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Dataframe improvements (elferherrera)
Content:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3894] datetime commands
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3907] describe command
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3960] rolling and cumulative commands
’Щ@1f5b7bb02769716ff4d4975d3669b009d1a6fdf798eb02063682fa1ef10bb06cЪxTitle: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Important bugfixes (lily-mara, gwenn, sophiajt)
Content:
A long-standing issue with history getting garbled when you have multiple shells open sending history updates is hopefully 
[link: https://github.com/kkawakam/rustyline/pull/560] now fixed
. Thanks to the rustyline maintainers for helping find the root cause and creating a fix for it.
’Щ@0442c0f6785210655e545c12100c9b3245c3adeed850a9781ea41ebb9607780cЪ%Title: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Additional improvements
Content:
waldyrious fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3890] a typo
, and fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3891] issue templates
fdncred started a list of 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3895] projects that officially support Nushell
RealCundo added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3888] PartialEq to ReturnValue
hedonihilist improved 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3902] how DirInfo calculates directory size
soumil-07 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3905] worked around a BigDecimal issue that broke 
``math floor``
sophiajt added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3906] ``in``
 and 
``not-in``
 for strings
, changed the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3924] release build to focus on binary size
baoyachi 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3914] updated shadow-rs, which fixes some datetime issues and more
knottio added 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3921] trailing slash when completing symlinked directory
fdncred fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3923] ``fetch``
 to better follow redirects
, and improved the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3962] issue template
filaretov fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3936] unaliasing to only affect the current scope
kubouch fixed 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3939] an issue where 
``source``
 couldn't handle paths with emojis
’Щ@49c6cd67b00775c726963c9cd78ed66e844f5ac3799d12b9763c09f8bf97003aЪјTitle: title: Nushell 0.36
Path: Looking ahead
Content:
The ability to search help and improve a built-in tutorial gives us a lot of opportunities to make Nushell more user-friendly, especially to users who are just getting started learning what Nushell can do. If you're interested, these are some good places to 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/blob/main/crates/nu-command/src/commands/core_commands/tutor.rs] jump in and help
 if you have specific topics or areas of interest.
The projects we reported on last time, engine-q and reedline, are steadily improving. We're currently working through any remaining issues so that we can begin experimenting with integrating them into Nushell.
